The course gives a general introduction to the fields of law which are relevant in international business, including contract law, international dispute resolution, European Union competition law, intellectual property law and company law. The teaching and learning methods that are used are interactive lectures, seminars and independent learning, including independent reading and written homeworks.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide students of economics and other non-legal studies with a general overview of the fields of law which are relevant in international business, and to give them the basic knowledge and practical skills for solving the most common legal problems which arise in the course of international trade.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student: 1) has a good general overview of the fields of law and the specific legal and practical issues which are relevant in international business and trade; 2) has basic knowledge about contract law, the different methods for resolving international disputes, European Union competition law, intellectual property law and company law; 3) can apply the acquired knowledge in practice by analysing and solving simple practical cases; 4) can propose practical and legally correct solutions to different legal problems which a company might face in the course of international business and trade; 5) can provide critical analysis on the different topics discussed during the course.
